;フラッシュ


I felt like the air had been sucked out of me.

At that moment, even I understood that the barrier had clearly been closed.

The human world and this world were separated, and the connection was closed without a trace.

"...Hahaha, I wonder what kind of trick this is. It disappeared even though it wasn't even walking away."

I muttered, not intending for anyone to hear.

The forest was flooded with light, and then I had no idea how they vanished.

I felt inexplicable, as if I was dreaming or had been tricked by some demon.

"...No, maybe it was all a dream."

The hut was burned down and there is no sign of their existence.

It seems impossible that he could have met elves and lived with them in a forest where humans could not enter.

It couldn't be a convenient dream that the first elf I met loved me so much.

No one would believe me if I told anyone. Those happy days have turned into a dream.

"......Ugh."

I dropped to my knees in disappointment on the spot.

I was lonely.

The days I spent with Hinata and the others felt so happy, so this made me feel even more lonely and miserable.

I don't think I'll ever find someone who loves me that much again.

The world has been closed off.

Those happy days will never come back.

It disappeared along with the burnt mountain hut.

"...Don't go, please don't go."

Reaching out in the direction where Hinata had disappeared, he realized that his fingertips would not reach anything, so he clenched his hand.

It was me who couldn't take Hinata's outstretched hand.

The truth is, I wanted to be with you forever...until my life ended.

But I was scared of making Hinata unhappy... No, that's not it. I was scared of being blamed for making Hinata unhappy, so I didn't take his hand.

Who would blame me?

I was just a coward.

The happier his memories with Hinata and the others were, the greater his fear of losing them.

I was just afraid of losing it.

...Because, I'm sure there's no way I can protect Hinata in this world. Right?

"I really wish you hadn't gone, Hinata."

No matter how much I lament here, there's no way my words will reach Hinata now that the world has been cut off.

Even though Hinata's voice calling out to me, saying he wanted to be with me, still rang in my ears, it was me who was unable to respond.

Until the very end, until the world was cut off, I remained indecisive and even blamed others for my inability to choose anything.

I continued to cry as I knelt on the ground.

